---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/UI/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/UI/Footer.astro';

const title = "Psychiatric follow-up in Athens";
const description = "Personalized psychiatric follow-up in central Athens. Diagnosis, pharmacotherapy and continuous assessment based on your clinical and genetic data.";
const canonicalURL = "https://drgkikas.com/en/ypiresies/psychiatriki-parakolouthisi";

const schemaBundle = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "MedicalProcedure",
      "name": title,
      "description": description,
      "url": canonicalURL
    },
    {
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://drgkikas.com/en" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Services", "item": "https://drgkikas.com/en/ypiresies" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": title, "item": canonicalURL }
      ]
    }
  ]
});
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} schema={schemaBundle}>
  <Header />
  <main class="pt-24 pb-16 bg-slate-50 min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      
      <!-- Breadcrumbs UI -->
      <nav class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-8 mt-4">
        <ol class="list-none p-0 inline-flex flex-wrap items-center">
          <li class="flex items-center"><a href="/en" class="hover:text-blue-700 transition-colors">Home</a><svg class="w-3 h-3 mx-2 opacity-50" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M7.293 14.707a1 1 0 010-1.414L10.586 10 7.293 6.707a1 1 0 011.414-1.414l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></li>
          <li class="flex items-center"><a href="/en/ypiresies/" class="hover:text-blue-700 transition-colors">Services</a><svg class="w-3 h-3 mx-2 opacity-50" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M7.293 14.707a1 1 0 010-1.414L10.586 10 7.293 6.707a1 1 0 011.414-1.414l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></li>
          <li class="flex items-center"><span class="text-slate-800 font-medium">{title}</span></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <div class="glass-card p-10 md:p-16">
        <div class="text-center mb-16 border-b border-slate-200 pb-12">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-8 leading-normal">{title}</h1>
          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-slate-600 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mx-auto">{description}</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="prose prose-lg md:prose-xl prose-blue max-w-none text-slate-700
          prose-p:mb-10 prose-p:leading-[1.9]
          prose-headings:text-blue-900 prose-headings:font-bold 
          prose-h2:mt-20 prose-h2:mb-8 prose-h2:border-b prose-h2:border-slate-100 prose-h2:pb-4
          prose-h3:mt-14 prose-h3:mb-6
          prose-a:font-bold prose-a:text-blue-900 prose-a:bg-blue-100 prose-a:px-2 prose-a:py-0.5 prose-a:rounded-lg prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:bg-blue-700 hover:prose-a:text-white prose-a:transition-colors
          prose-ul:my-10 prose-li:my-5 marker:text-blue-500">
          
          <p class="font-bold">Correct diagnosis, personalized treatment, continuous assessment — not simple prescription renewal.</p>

          <h2>What psychiatric follow-up includes</h2>
          <p>Psychiatric follow-up is not a single visit. It is an ongoing therapeutic relationship that evolves as your condition evolves. In the clinic, every first visit begins with a complete clinical assessment: history, symptoms, previous treatments and level of functioning. We do not rush. We do not skip steps.</p>

          <h2>What is assessed during the first visit?</h2>
          <p>During the initial assessment, we examine:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Complete psychiatric and medical history</li>
            <li>Current psychiatric disorders and their severity</li>
            <li>Medications previously used and your response to them</li>
            <li>Possible genetic causes of medication intolerance or non-response through PGx</li>
            <li>Sleep, anxiety manifestations and physical symptoms</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>How regular follow-up works</h2>
          <p>Follow-up does not mean automatic prescription renewal. Each session reassesses:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Treatment effectiveness using validated psychometric tools, such as PHQ-9, GAD-7, HAM-D and others</li>
            <li>Side effects that may require adjustment</li>
            <li>The need to add additional therapeutic or supportive methods, such as rTMS, tDCS, psychotherapy, light therapy or PGx analysis</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Who is it suitable for?</h2>
          <p>Psychiatric follow-up is intended for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>People with new psychiatric symptoms who seek correct diagnosis from the beginning</li>
            <li>Patients with chronic psychiatric disorders, such as depression, bipolar disorder, OCD or anxiety disorders, who have not stabilized with previous treatments</li>
            <li>People with resistant symptoms who want to understand whether there may be a genetic reason for non-response to medication</li>
            <li>Patients undergoing rTMS who need integrated psychiatric follow-up during the protocol</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="mt-20 pt-12 border-t border-slate-200">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-8">FAQ</h2>
            <div class="space-y-8">
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">How long does the first visit last?</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600">The initial assessment lasts 40 minutes, plus the time required for psychometric tools. A careful evaluation requires time.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Do I need a referral?</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600">No. You can book an appointment directly without referral from another physician.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Are online follow-up visits available?</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600">Yes. Follow-up visits — not the first assessment — can also take place remotely via secure video call.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">What if the medications do not work?</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600">This is exactly the scenario in which Pharmacogenomics and rTMS are most relevant. We do not stop at the prescription. We look for the reason.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">How often does follow-up take place?</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600">It depends on the treatment phase. In the acute phase: every 2–4 weeks. In the stabilization phase: every 1–3 months.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-900 text-white p-8 md:p-12 rounded-3xl mt-16 shadow-xl">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-300 mb-6">My approach</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed italic">“I do not treat diagnoses; I treat people. Each patient has a different biological profile, history and set of needs. The combination of clinical assessment, psychometric measurement and — when needed — genetic analysis allows treatment plans that are not based on the statistical majority, but on the data of the specific person in front of me.”</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Internal Links for SEO -->
        <div class="mt-20 pt-12 border-t border-slate-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-8">Related Services</h2>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <a href="/en/ypiresies/pgx/" class="p-6 bg-blue-50 rounded-2xl border border-blue-100 hover:border-blue-300 transition-all font-bold text-blue-900">Pharmacogenomics (PGx) &rarr;</a>
            <a href="/en/ypiresies/psychotherapeia/" class="p-6 bg-blue-50 rounded-2xl border border-blue-100 hover:border-blue-300 transition-all font-bold text-blue-900">Psychotherapy &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
